  • 24/7 Professional Security Monitoring - Get a text or call from a professional security agent in 5 seconds (yes, seconds) or less after an alarm is triggered. If an emergency is confirmed or they can’t reach you, 911 will be alerted and help sent immediately.
  • Easy DIY Installation - Do-it-yourself home security has never been easier. Every security and monitoring sensor connects wirelessly to the Wyze Sense Hub, so just peel, stick, and you’re done!
  • Easy to Use App - With our beloved industry-leading app experience, you can control and monitor your home’s status anywhere anytime. Arm/disarm your home remotely, view Wyze Cam feeds, set up automatic security schedules, and check the history of your home’s sensors.
  • Easily Expandable - Our system supports up to 100 sensors and expanding is as easy as peel-and-stick. Customize your monitoring system to your exact home, or just add more sensors as your needs change. You can even add Wyze Sense Climate and Leak Sensors to your system to make sure your home is safe from Mother Nature too.
  • $9.99/month. No hidden fees. - Professional home security shouldn’t just be for the wealthy. At Wyze, we believe deeply in providing quality technology at a price anyone can afford. At $9.99/month, our service is a fraction of the market average. The monitoring service is only available for the 50 US States at this time.

        Never wanted to have a negative or avoid or dislike option...until now.

        I have been using WYZE cameras for years - so I thought maybe they will produce an inexpensive alarm system. WRONG!

        Summary of issues:
        1) Installation - Door Sensor - design failure and no extra sticky material provided.
        They only provide the pressure sensor attachment, unlike other alarm systems that include an optional plastic holder with screws. Door molding prevented installation level, stuck it to the molding - the door caught the sensor - so had to try to install again. But tape would not stick again - and no extra provided. So now I have a sensor dangling, might fall off and setoff alarm by accident. No optional plastic holder was provided that would allow sturdy screw installation. (Simplisafe describes EXACTLY what should be designed - read WYZE designers!)

        2) Installation - Hub - Reset button. Not sure if WYZE has bugs in firmware, but if you accidently touch for 1 second the reset button which is raised on back. You have to delete all devices and setup again. Attempted to contact HELP, but unavailable for 3 days due to Rai typhoon. Found blog, followed suggestion to hold reset for 13 seconds - did not solve, had to delete and re-setup all devices

        3) Motion Sensor - Cheap and useless. Unless you have no windows with zero sunlight, throw this away. Set on Lowest sensitivity, with shades down and on sunny day, triggers motion sensor incorrectly every 5 minutes.

        4) Alarm company - Issue 1 - Does not provide Caller ID or what number will contact you
        So when they call you - you have no idea if it is a telemarketer or company - shows up just as a foreign number

        5) Alarm company - Issue 2 - Does not provide details of WHO they will contact in the event of an emergency - just you are "all set" Well guess what idiots, my house has a local township and you called the STATE Police!! No where in app or

        6) Alarm company - Issue 3 - You can NOT call the foreign alarm system spams call number BACK - it is only outgoing. You ONLY can disable alarm is from App. AND though app tells you it is disarmed and you are "All Set" guess what, they did NOT cancel.

        So I ended up with alarm company with random number calling me, they did leave message, I attempted to call back, unable, 2 minutes after alarm went off, I disabled from app. But they did not cancel and they are contacting the WRONG jurisdiction. Waiting for a bill in the mail

        I wish i never purchased a product from a company that has NO business or understanding of what a security system is to be designed or proper procedures.
